Cairn scavenger expulsion
-1 3 1 10 60 72 3440 3800 4 1400000 0
5770
Cairn scavengers are systematically stripping Measure's Rest of survey tablets and historical records that the Kowloon Jade Clerk commission has been funding expeditions to recover. The scavenger clan has grown large enough to hold the library complex against individual patrols, and continued losses will render the Reach cartographic archive permanently incomplete. The Kowloon postmaster requires a significant kill count before committing a full expulsion detail.
The cairn scavenger presence at Measure's Rest has been reduced below operational density. The Kowloon postmaster has dispatched a recovery team to secure the remaining survey tablet collection on behalf of the Jade Clerk commission, and a provisional inventory is underway to assess what records were lost. The expulsion operation has been logged as a standing precedent for future archive defense protocols.

